## Assessment Areas

1. **Dependency Handling**: Did agents proactively communicate about inter-feature dependencies? When backend work was needed before frontend could proceed, did agents coordinate the handoff? Were there delays caused by poor dependency communication?
2. **Resource Allocation**: Did the team discuss and align on resource priorities? When constraints appeared (budget, time), did agents adapt their allocation? Were there signs of siloed work or misaligned priorities?
3. **Handoff Quality**: When work passed between agents (e.g. backend completing a feature that frontend depends on), was the handoff smooth? Did agents communicate readiness, blockers, and expectations?

## What to Look For

- Proactive dependency announcements ("I'll need X to be done before I can start Y")
- Responsive acknowledgment of dependency requests
- Resource priority discussions and alignment
- Smooth transitions between phases (development -> QA -> launch readiness)
- Signs of wasted effort (working on features with unmet dependencies)
- Signs of misalignment (agents working on low-priority items while high-priority items are blocked)

